    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-03-04T16:42:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-03-04T16:42:00-05:00" n="409"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d409">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.86/3–452: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>No. 409<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Certain Diplomatic Missions</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d409fn1">Sent to Cairo, Baghdad, Jidda, Amman, Beirut,
                        Damascus, Tel Aviv, London, Paris, Ankara, and Karachi.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-03-04T16:42:00-05:00"
                            >March 4, 1952—4:42 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>758. Dept interested recent developments <gloss target="#t_NE1">NE</gloss>
                    connected with Arab-Israel relations and refers fol: Iraqi <gloss
                        target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_ASN1">Nuri</persName>’s remarks as reported by UK rep
                    Baghdad that Arab Collective Security Pact might be framed as instrument of
                    defense against aggressive threats external to <gloss target="#t_ME1">ME</gloss>
                    rather than against Israel (Baghdad <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss>
                    682 Feb 27):<note n="2" xml:id="d409fn2">Not printed.</note> recent mtg <gloss
                        target="#t_Leb1">Leb</gloss> rep with Gen <persName corresp="#p_YMG1"
                        >Yadin</persName> and actions and comments <persName corresp="#p_TTAB1"
                        >Ahmad Touqan</persName>, Jordan rep Israel–Jordan <gloss target="#t_MAC1"
                        >MAC</gloss> (Tel Aviv Emb tels 881 Feb 27 and 894 Feb 29 and Amman <gloss
                        target="#t_Legtel1">Legtel</gloss> 244 Feb 29). Israel reps Wash currently
                    stressing that Egypt reps at <gloss target="#t_UNGA1">UNGA</gloss> Paris
                    considerably more moderate toward Pal question than other Arab reps and in
                    private talks with Israel reps indicated steps improve Israel-Egypt relations
                    might be possible near future. Israel interest also aroused by alleged remarks
                        <persName corresp="#p_ZKSM1">Zafrullah</persName> in Cairo (Tel Aviv <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 897 Feb 29,<note n="3" xml:id="d409fn3"
                        >Telegram 897 from Tel Aviv, Feb. 29, referred to a statement reported to
                        have been made during a recent visit to Cairo by <persName
                            corresp="#p_ZKSM1">Zafrullah Khan</persName>, the Pakistani Minister of
                        Foreign Affairs and Commonwealth Relations, that the settlement of
                        Arab-Israeli differences was essential to regional collective security. The
                        telegram reported that the Israeli Government was particularly interested in
                        knowing the extent to which the statement might be interpreted as an
                        indication that Egypt might be preparing ground for possible conversations
                        with Israel, or other steps toward the improvement of relations.
                        (684A.86/2–2952)</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> to Cairo 1350 Mar 3<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d409fn4">Telegram 1350 to Cairo, Mar. 3, requested a text of
                            <persName corresp="#p_ZKSM1">Zafrullah</persName>’s remarks.
                        (684A.86/3–352)</note>). <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> Israel Amb
                        <persName corresp="#p_EAS1">Eban</persName> intends discuss these
                    developments with <gloss target="#t_Secy1">Secy</gloss> morning Mar 6.</p>
                <p>While gratified these indications relaxation Arab-Israel tensions <gloss
                        target="#t_NE1">NE</gloss>, Dept inclined view with reservation
                    possibilities any concrete progress toward peace settlements at this time view
                    past history this problem and other factors such as Anglo-Egyptian question.</p>
                <p>Request addressee missions comment soonest.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
